CNCP v1 22886
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#7999: Fallback attributes for slots",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:24:43.887990+00:00",
  "text": "Fallback attributes for slots\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\n\nThe fallback attributes work for child components that's fine.\r\nThe problem I intuitively wanted them to work for slots:\r\n\r\n```\r\n// FormRow.vue\r\n<template>\r\n    <slot class=\"form-row-col\"></slot>\r\n</template>\r\n\r\n// I hoped all children will be assigned the class form-row-col:\r\n<template>\r\n    <smart-form :data=\"user\">\r\n        <form-row>\r\n            <form-input name=\"name\"></form-input>\r\n            <form-input name=\"email\"></form-input>\r\n        </form-row>\r\n    </smart-form>\r\n</template>\r\n```\r\nMoreover the problem is exaggerated by multiple slot children...\r\nI would like to have some simple solution for this problem.\r\nAny workaround by the way?\r\nI definitely dont want to use scoped slots here and fallback the class manually.\n\n### What does the proposed API look like?\n\nMake support for fallback attributes for slots.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request"
  ],
